In [52]:
# Generating multiple clusters with varying cluster sizes using spectral clustering and K-Means
f = plt.figure()
f.add_subplot(2, 2, 1)
for i in range(2, 6):
    spec_clust = SpectralClustering(n_clusters=i)
    spec_clust.fit(x)
    f.add_subplot(2, 2, i-1)
    plt.scatter(x[:,0], x[:,1], s=5, c=spec_clust.labels_, label="Spectral clustering with "+str(i)+" clusters")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    kmeans = KMeans(init="random", n_clusters=i, n_init=10, max_iter=300, random_state=42)
    kmeans.fit(x)
    f.add_subplot(2, 2, i-1)
    plt.scatter(x[:,0], x[:,1], s=5, c=kmeans.labels_, label="KMeans clustering with "+str(i)+" clusters")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
